sub_title: Assistant Professor at Eindhoven University of Technology
summary:
Stella develops data-driven mathematical models and uses them to make better decisions.

Stella Kapodistria (PhD cum laude 2009, University of Athens, Greece) is an assistant professor in the section Stochastics of the Department of Mathematics and Computer Science  in Eindhoven University of Technology (TU/e). Since 2014 she is a member of the Networks project and she is involved in the research program Smart Maintenance of the Data Science Center of TU/e under the Data Science Flagship, a strategic cooperation between  Philips and the TU/e.
